CodeList.Name: Non-system Reason for PCI Delay

Description.TranslatedText: A terminology codelist that contains reasons for non-system PCI delay.

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: Cardiac arrest which occurs before a percutaneous coronary intervention can take place.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Cardiac Arrest Prior to Percutaneous Coronary Intervention

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: Access to the subject's vasculature is troublesome or formidable.

EnumeratedItem.CodedValue: DIFFICULTY CROSSING THE CULPRIT LESION DURING THE PCI PROCEDURE
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: Placement of intracoronary devices across the coronary stenosis is troublesome or formidable.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Difficulty Crossing Culprit Lesion During Percutaneous Coronary Intervention

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: Endotracheal intubation which occurs before a percutaneous coronary intervention can take place.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Endotracheal Intubation before Percutaneous Coronary Intervention

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: Different than the one(s) previously specified or mentioned. (NCI)
The subject has not provided consent in a timely manner for the procedure to take place.

CodeList.nciodm:PreferredTerm: CDISC SDTM Non-system Reason for PCI Delay Terminology
